@TITLE "MMURENDER(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name mmurender - Convert modules to other audio formats @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}mmurender@{"ub"} [@{"i"}generaloptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}outputoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}qualityoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}otheroptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}MODFILE...@{"ui"}] @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description @{"b"}mmurender@{"ub"} loads @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s and converts its to other digital audio format. If no @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}s is given then module will be loaded from standard input. If no @{"b"}-o@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--output@{"ub"} or @{"b"}-B@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--batch@{"ub"} option is given, then result audio data will be send to standard output. 

@{"b"}mmurender@{"ub"} is part of the MikMod Utilities package, and uses MikMod Sound Library to load and render modules. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Exit Status @{"b"}mmurender@{"ub"} uses standard exit status, as defined in sysexits.h. See a description of all exit codes in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}General Options See a description of all general options in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}Output Options @{"b"}-o, --output=@{"ub"}@{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} Send the output data to @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"}. The default is to send data to standard output. This option cannot be combined with the @{"b"}--batch@{"ub"} option. @{"b"}-B, --batch@{"ub"} Convert multiple modules to multiple files. If this option is given, then @{"b"}mmurender@{"ub"} will split the output into multiple files. Output file names are identical to corresponding input file names with suffix (extension) replaced with suffix of output audio format. For example, "music.mod" will be converted to "music.wav". If this option is not given then all input files will be converted to the single stream. This option cannot be combined with the @{"b"}-o@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--output@{"ub"} option. @{"b"}-t, --type=@{"ub"}@{"i"}TYPE@{"ui"} Specify output audio format. Specify @{"b"}help@{"ub"} as argument to get a list of all possible output audio formats. If audiofile support is not present (this is configured at compile-time), then only raw audio format is available, that is the raw audio data with no header information. The default is to use raw output format. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Quality Options @{"b"}-r, --mixfreq=@{"ub"}@{"i"}RATE@{"ui"} Sound playback frequency, in hertz. High values yield high sound quality, but need more computing power than lower values. The default value is 44100 Hz, which is compact disc quality. Other common values are 22100 Hz (radio quality), 11025 Hz (phone quality), and 8000 Hz (mu-law quality). @{"b"}-s, --stereo@{"ub"} Select stereo sound. This is the default. @{"b"}-m, --mono@{"ub"} Select mono sound. @{"b"}-1, --16bit@{"ub"} Select 16 bit sound mode. This mode yields better sound quality, but needs twice more mixing time, in comparison with 8 bit sound mode. The default is to use 16 bit sound mode. @{"b"}-8, --8bit@{"ub"} Select 8 bit sound mode. @{"b"}-h, --hqmixer@{"ub"} Select the high-quality software mixer. This mode yields better sound quality, but needs more mixing time. @{"b"}-H, --nohqmixer@{"ub"} Disable high-quality software mixer. This is the default. @{"b"}-p, --pansep=@{"ub"}@{"i"}PANSEP@{"ui"} Set stereo channels separation to @{"i"}PANSEP@{"ui"}. Allowed values range from 0 (no separation, thus mono sound) to 128 (full channel separation). The default value is 128. @{"b"}-e, --reverb=@{"ub"}@{"i"}REVERB@{"ui"} Set amount of sound reverberation to @{"i"}REVERB@{"ui"}. Allowed values range from 0 (no reverberation) to 15 (a rough estimate for chaos...). The default value is 0. @{"b"}-i, --interp@{"ub"} Enable the interpolated mixers. Interpolated mixing gives better sound but takes a bit more time than standard mixing. If the MikMod library is built with the high quality mixer, interpolated mixing is always enabled, regardless of this option. @{"b"}-I, --nointerp@{"ub"} Disable the interpolated mixers. @{"b"}-u, --surround@{"ub"} Enable the surround mixers. Since surround mixing works only for stereo sound, this option has no effect if the sound playback is in mono. @{"b"}-U, --nosurround@{"ub"} Disable the surround mixers. @{"b"}-n, --maxchan=@{"ub"}@{"i"}MAXCH@{"ui"} The maximum number of channels the song is allowed to request from the mixer. @{" " link "'#toc7'/MAIN"}Other Options @{"b"}-v, --volume=@{"ub"}@{"i"}VOLUME@{"ui"} Set sound volume to @{"i"}VOLUME@{"ui"}. Allowed values range from 0 to 128. The default value is 128. @{"b"}--reverse@{"ub"} Exchange the left and right stereo channels. @{"b"}-c, --curious@{"ub"} Enable curiosity level. If this option is given the following things occur: pattern positions occurring after the "end of song" marker in S3M and IT modules are loaded, and the end of song is set to the last position; hidden extra patterns are searched in MOD modules, and if found, played after the last "official" pattern; MED modules with synthsounds are loaded without causing the MMERR_MED_SYNTHSAMPLES, and synthsounds are mapped to an empty sample. @{"b"}-S, --skip=@{"ub"}@{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} Skip @{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} patterns from beginning of each module. @{"b"}-C, --count=@{"ub"}@{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} Process only @{"i"}NUMBER@{"ui"} patterns of each module. @{"b"}-T, --filesfrom=@{"ub"}@{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} Read module list from @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"}. Each line of @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} is a module file name. Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored. If @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} is -, then list will be loaded from standard input. @{"b"}-X, --filesfromcmd=@{"ub"}@{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"} Read module list from output of @{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"}. The @{"i"}COMMAND@{"ui"} will be passed to the shell (/bin/sh -c). Each line of output is a module file name. Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored. @{"b"}-G, --progress@{"ub"} Show progress on stderr. @{" " link "'#toc8'/MAIN"}Examples Convert "music.mod" to the raw audio data and write result to "music.raw" file: @{"b"}mmurender -o music.raw music.mod@{"ub"} 

Convert all "*.xm" files to "*.wav" files: @{"b"}mmurender --batch -t wav *.xm@{"ub"} 

Convert "music1.it" and "music2.mod" to Ogg Vorbis format and write result to "music1_2.ogg": @{"b"}mmurender -t wav music1.it music2.mod |oggenc -o music1_2.ogg -@{"ub"} @{" " link "'#toc9'/MAIN"}Notes Some defaults of @{"i"}quality options@{"ui"} can be changed at compile-time. To get information about compile-time configuration use @{"b"}mmu --version@{"ub"} command. 

When using the raw audio format the sample data is made of unsigned values in 8 bit sound mode, and signed little-endian values in 16 bit sound mode. @{" " link "'#toc10'/MAIN"}Bugs If you found any, please let me known. @{" " link "'#toc11'/MAIN"}Author Konstantin Korikov <lostclus@ua.fm> @{" " link "'#toc12'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'mmu.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mikmod.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mikmod(1)@{"ub"} 


